Convert Mini HDMI to HDMI

UGREEN Mini HDMI male to HDMI female cable is ideal for connecting camcorder, camera, laptop, video card or tablet with Mini HDMI port to HDMI compatible TV, HDTV, monitor or projector. Enable you viewing hi-definition video or image at home, office or conference room.

Widely Compatibility

HDMI-MINI also known as Type C HDMI port is compatible with Raspberry Pi Zero, Pi zero w, Lenovo ThinkPad Yoga 12 inch laptop, NUC barebones desktop, Geforce GT 430 graphics card, video card, camcorder, Nvidia Shield K1 tablet, pico projector, Sony HDR-XR500, Nikon D3200, Nikon D810, DSLR and more canon cameras with mini hdmi.

HDMI also known as Type A HDMI standard port is widely used for LCD TV, HDTV, monitor, display, projector and more.

4K and 1080P Supported

Support up to 4K 60Hz, maximum UHD 3840×2160 and compatible with lower resolution including 2560x1600, 2560x1440, 1920x1200, 1080p etc.

Mini hdmi to hdmi cable transfers high-definition video and image from portable device to your big screen HDTV or computer monitor.

Support Audio Video Sync

Support Audio Return Channel (ARC), HDMI Ethernet Channel (HEC), 32 channel audio, Dolby True audio and 3D video.

Eliminate the need for a separate audio cable and ensure the quality of digital audio.

Important Notes

To achieve 4K video resolution, it requires 4K source, qualified HDMI cable and output display which both can support 4K.

This adapter can convert mini-hdmi interface to hdmi female, so an extra hdmi male cable is required(sold separately) when connecting TV.

      1.0 out of 5 stars Warning: This is STANDARD to MINI not MINI to STANDARD!
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 25, 2019
      Verified Purchase
      Hey guys, not the end of the world but this is NOT a 'mini hdmi to standard hdmi' - this is a standard to mini! HDMI goes in... Mini-HDMI comes out... Especially confusing as the 3rd picture on product page definitely shows a MALE MINI-HDMI going into a FEMALE MINI-HDMI port and the last picture appears to be a full size STANDARD MALE HDMI lead.

      I now understand the pictures are simply there for educational purposes and do NOT actually represent the product you are buying. Together with the term 'to' (which assumes male to female and never female to male as female sockets cannot be used to connect to devices which are ALWAYS female ports) this is very confusing.

      Not worth either of our time to send back. I recommend you change name to correct adaptor. Thank you and so sorry for negative feedback! Did look rather silly for a couple of days at work with an overly long cable from my TV :/
